# Formspree integration decision

## Selected guide: Vanilla JavaScript (AJAX)

The portfolio is a static website built with HTML, CSS, and plain JavaScript and deployed through GitHub Pages. It is not a React application and has no JavaScript bundler.

The integration therefore uses the Vanilla JavaScript approach, but keeps the implementation dependency-free rather than loading `@formspree/ajax` from a CDN. The existing site script already manages form state and can submit directly to Formspree with the browser `fetch()` API.

## Why this implementation fits the site

- No new framework or build step
- No external JavaScript dependency
- Inline success and error messages
- Accessible `aria-live` status updates
- Native browser validation
- Normal HTML submission remains available as a fallback
- Destination email remains private in Formspree

